import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.countplot(y='country', data=data, order=data['country'].value_counts().index, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Airports')
    plt.ylabel('Country')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="state", data=data, order=data['state'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set(xlabel='State/Province', ylabel='Number of Airports')
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by state/province?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['name_length'] = data['name'].apply(len)
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='name_length', color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(x=data['name_length'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(x=data['name_length'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names by length?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Length of Airport Names')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['city']).agg({'iata': 'count', 'latitude': 'mean', 'longitude': 'mean', 'population': 'mean'}).reset_index()
    sns.scatterplot(x='population', y='iata', data=data, hue='iata', palette='viridis')
    plt.axvline(data['population'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median population')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by city size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Number of airports')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
